NUMBER 1865
NAME Health Clinic

INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
This spotless room is a remedial and preventative clinic for all residents
of the poor quarter. Partitions are skillfully arranged to provide privacy
for various patients. Two beds are set up for overnight patients near the
rear of the room. A plaque is on the wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 65 VAL1=10 UNLOCKED VAL2=1864 VAL3=1861 ADJ1=347
ITEM 1 400
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 1
The Poor Quarter Restoration Society pledges that medical care shall be
provided free. Funds specifically for the children provided with love by
Duchess Camorra Amadeus.
*DESCRIPTION_END

NUMBER 1866
NAME Job Center

INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
This smallish room has several desks for job counselors to work with the
residents of the Poor Quarter in obtaining employment. A chalkboard lists
various jobs, mostly involving cleanup of the Poor Quarter itself.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 65 ADJ1=40 VAL1=10 UNLOCKED VAL2=1864 VAL3=1861

NUMBER 1867
NAME Day Care Center

INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT

*DESCRIPTION_START
This vast area is mostly a large playground. Various implements of
recreation are scattered hereabout. Some items are recognizable as slides,
see-saws and other toys. Others seem to be there just to climb and play
on, in whatever fashion strikes the youngsters. A sizable corner is
partitioned off for crafts and other less vigorous activities. A plaque is
on the side of the partition.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GAZE -1
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You are startled to notice that the ceiling is in fact about forty feet above your head here as you gaze at the naked roof of the renovated warehouse.
ENDIF

